name: Stray Kids
description: Stray Kids is a self-producing K-Pop group known for their powerful performances, unique sound, and deep involvement in music production.

funFacts: Born in South Korea, raised in Sydney, Australia
Trained at JYP for 7 years before debut
Hosts weekly live stream 'Chan's Room'
Produces music as part of 3RACHA
Known as the group's 'dad' for taking care of members
members.bio: Bang Chan is the Australian-Korean leader of Stray Kids and head of their producing unit 3RACHA. After training for 7 years at JYP, he formed Stray Kids through the survival show. His 'Chan's Room' VLive series is beloved by STAYs worldwide.

funFacts: Has three cats: Soonie, Doongie, and Dori
Was a backup dancer for BTS before joining JYP
Known for his savage humor and witty remarks
Eliminated during survival show but brought back by members
Loves cooking and often makes food for members
members.bio: Lee Know is Stray Kids' main dancer known for his precise technique and cat-like charisma. Before JYP, he was a backup dancer for BTS. His sassy personality and love for his three cats make him a fan favorite.

funFacts: Raps under stage name SpearB in 3RACHA
Known for his dark, powerful rapping style
Has a cute personality despite his fierce image
Very physically strong despite small stature
Writes emotional, introspective lyrics
members.bio: Changbin is one-third of 3RACHA and known for his aggressive rap delivery. Despite his fierce stage presence as 'Dark Changbin,' he's actually quite soft and cuddly off-stage, earning him the nickname 'Muscular Rabbit.'

funFacts: Known for his elegant, artistic dancing style
Passionate about painting and visual art
Had a viral 'God's Menu' fancam with 40M+ views
Best friends with ENHYPEN's Sunoo and TXT's Yeonjun
His dog's name is Kkami
members.bio: Hyunjin is Stray Kids' visual and a main dancer known for his elegant, artistic movement. He's passionate about all forms of art including painting. His expressive dance style and visuals have made him one of K-pop's most popular idols.

funFacts: Known as the 'Quokka' for his resemblance to the animal
Part of producing unit 3RACHA as J.One
Can both rap fast and sing high notes
Has openly discussed his anxiety to help fans
Lived in Malaysia as a child
members.bio: Han is a versatile member who excels at both rapping and singing. As part of 3RACHA, he contributes significantly to Stray Kids' music. He's known for his adorable 'quokka' cheeks and has been open about his mental health journey.

funFacts: Born and raised in Sydney, Australia
Famous for his extremely deep voice contrast with cute looks
Known for his bright, sunshine personality
Loves baking - made famous 'fairy bread' in Australia
His Korean name is Yongbok
members.bio: Felix is the Australian-Korean member known for his surprisingly deep voice and sunshine personality. Despite struggling with Korean initially, he's become fluent and is beloved for his warmth. His freckles and bright smile are iconic among fans.

funFacts: Has perfect pitch and stable vocals
Big fan of Day6 before debut
Known as the group's mood maker
Resembles a puppy with his bright smile
Very organized and clean
members.bio: Seungmin is Stray Kids' vocal powerhouse with perfect pitch and incredibly stable live vocals. He's known as a 'puppy' for his bright, loyal personality and is the group's resident Day6 superfan.

funFacts: Known for his fox-like visuals and smile
Had braces during debut, removed in 2020
Despite being maknae, can be savage to hyungs
His laugh is contagious and unique
Trained for only 2 years before debut
members.bio: I.N is the maknae of Stray Kids with signature fox-like visuals and bread cheeks. Despite being the youngest, he's known for his witty comebacks to his hyungs. His vocal improvement over the years has been praised by fans.
